        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "over the deofrxlainhtahppn\"r mockingbird,findingher young in a cage,wil sometimes bring it porson berries)he thinks it be forhr youtda to live in captivity.\"",
          "block_bbox": [
            101,
            266,
            2033,
            655
          ],
          "block_id": 1,
          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "E \n\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            286,
            671,
            1566,
            770
          ],
          "block_id": 2,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "A.studies birds B.loves creatures C.maors in habit D.takescareof trees ornithologist这个词从未见过，但通过他的语言，可判断出这是一个对鸟很有研究的人。我很爱写，把鸟装在笼里，细心照料，而且鸟的母亲也飞过来喂这只鸟，但这只鸟却死了，我很不理解。到我家来的这个人给我详细解释了写死的原因，说明这个人非常懂写。据此，选A。",
          "block_bbox": [
            102,
            768,
            2033,
            1282
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "利用主题问解阅读理解题",
          "block_bbox": [
            557,
            1397,
            1323,
            1490
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "最有效的办法是找出主题句。一篇文章通常都是围绕一个中心意思展开的。而这个中心意思往往由一个句子来概括。这个能概括文章或段落中心意思的句子叫主题句。因此，理解一个段落或一篇文章的中心意思首先要学会寻找主题句。主题句一般具有三个特点：",
          "block_bbox": [
            65,
            1503,
            2024,
            1902
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(1)概括性强：表述的意思比较概括。",
          "block_bbox": [
            77,
            1926,
            1176,
            2008
          ],
          "block_id": 6,
          "block_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(2)结构简单：句子结构较简单，多数都不采用长、难句的形式。",
          "block_bbox": [
            77,
            2026,
            1752,
            2114
          ],
          "block_id": 7,
          "block_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(3)受它支撑：段落中其他句子用来解释、支撑或发展该句所表述的主题思想。\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            79,
            2124,
            2011,
            2315
          ],
          "block_id": 8,
          "block_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "在一篇短文或一个段落中，大部分主题句的位置情况有三种：",
          "block_bbox": [
            75,
            2336,
            1699,
            2426
          ],
          "block_id": 9,
          "block_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "一、主题句在段首或篇首",
          "block_bbox": [
            81,
            2444,
            739,
            2526
          ],
          "block_id": 10,
          "block_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "主题句在段首或篇首的情况相当普遍。一般新闻报道、说明文，议论文大都采用先总述，后分述的叙事方法。如：",
          "block_bbox": [
            66,
            2540,
            1997,
            2739
          ],
          "block_id": 11,
          "block_order": 11
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "A livingthing on theeart needother thi to liveNotin lives alone.Mostanimals mutlive in agroup,and eve a plantgrow close ",
          "block_bbox": [
            71,
            2758,
            2009,
            2974
          ],
          "block_id": 12,
          "block_order": 12
        },
        {
          "block_label": "number",
          "block_content": "C0",
          "block_bbox": [
